14 period for submitting a rebuttal statement an additional 10
15 business days for good cause. The secretary of state shall provide
16 a copy of the rebuttal statement to the person against whom the
17 complaint was filed. If, on review of the complaint, the secretary
18 of state determines that the complaint is frivolous, illegible,
19 indefinite, or unsigned, or does not identify an alleged violator,
20 allege a violation of the act, or contain a verification statement,
21 the secretary of state may summarily dismiss the complaint without
22 prejudice. If a complaint is summarily dismissed, the complainant
23 must be notified in writing as to the reason the complaint was
24 dismissed. The secretary of state may consolidate similar
25 complaints.
