2 a civil fine imposed under this act in the general fund. The
3 secretary of state may bring an action in circuit court to recover
4 the amount of a civil fine.
5 (12) The secretary of state shall review a report or statement
6 filed under this act and may investigate an apparent violation of
7 this act. If the secretary of state determines that there may be
8 reason to believe a violation of this act occurred and the
9 procedures prescribed in subsection (9) have been complied with,
10 the secretary of state may commence a hearing under subsection (10)
11 to determine whether a violation of this act occurred.
12 (13) There is no private right of action, either in law or in
13 equity, under this act. The remedies provided in this act are the
14 exclusive means by which this act may be enforced and by which any
15 harm resulting from a violation of this act may be redressed.
16 (14) The secretary of state shall preserve a report filed
17 under this act for 15 years after the date the report is filed. If
18 the secretary of state or attorney general determines under this
19 section that a violation of this act occurred, the secretary of
20 state shall preserve all complaints, orders, decisions, or other
21 documents related to that violation for 15 years after the date of
22 the determination or the date the violation is corrected, whichever
23 is later. Reports filed under this act may be reproduced under the
24 records reproduction act, 1992 PA 116, MCL 24.401 to 24.406. After
25 the required preservation period, the reports, or the reproductions
26 of the reports, may be disposed of in the manner prescribed in the
27 management and budget act, 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1101 to 18.1594, and
28 section 11 of the Michigan history center act, 2016 PA 470, MCL
29 399.811.
